  "cfo_summary": [
    "<strong>Total available cash is $103,126</strong> across all nine entities. After <strong>$37,412 in approved external payments</strong> and <strong>$33,020 in intercompany transfers</strong> this week, projected end-of-week balance is <strong>$65,714</strong>. The intercompany transfers include June management fees flowing into GRP ($25,611) and open lot insurance allocations flowing into CP ($7,409).",
    "<strong>GRP projects to $-3,654</strong> after receiving $25,611 in management fee deposits, partially offset by $13,426 in external payments and a starting available balance of negative $15,839 from pending transactions. <strong>Countryside projects to $6,745</strong> after paying the full open lot premium ($11,969) and receiving back $7,409 in allocations from WW, RE, CA, and DA.",
    "<strong>Winterwood projects to negative $7,664</strong> after its open lot allocation ($3,990), management fee ($4,509), and maintenance bills ($2,780). Country Aire projects to negative $475 after its open lot share and landscaping. Both need intercompany support. Decade Acres at $23,290 and Four Seasons at $29,855 are the strongest positions and the logical funding sources.",
    "<strong>No BvA this week</strong> \u2014 P&L export was not available. BvA will resume next week. The WW closings and FS2:01 financing remain the primary near-term cash events. The two National Flood Experts invoices ($34,650 total) remain on hold pending Tim's approval."
  ],
